edu.stanford.nlp.ling.tokensregex

Class Env

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.stanford.nlp.ling.tokensregex.Env

  • public class Env
extends Object
    Holds environment variables to be used for compiling string into a pattern. Use EnvLookup to perform actual lookup (it will provide reasonable defaults)

    Some of the types of variables to bind are:

    • SequencePattern (compiled pattern)
    • PatternExpr (sequence pattern expression - precompiled)
    • NodePattern (pattern for matching one element)
    • Class (binding of CoreMap attribute to java Class)

      • defaultTokensResultAnnotationKey

        public List<Class> defaultTokensResultAnnotationKey
        List of keys indicating the per-token annotations (default is null). If specified, each token will be annotated with the extracted results from the defaultResultsAnnotationExtractor. If null, then individual tokens that are matched are not annotated.

      • defaultResultAnnotationKey

        public List<Class> defaultResultAnnotationKey
        List of keys indicating what fields should be annotated for the aggregated coremap. If specified, the aggregated coremap is annotated with the extracted results from the defaultResultsAnnotationExtractor. If null, then the aggregated coremap is not annotated.

      • defaultNestedResultsAnnotationKey
